adjectives.description: rarefied (comparative more rarefied, superlative most rarefied)

entries.meaning: Distant from the lives and everyday concerns of ordinary people; esoteric, exclusive, select.
examples: Philosophical debates can be quite rarefied.

entries.meaning: Elevated in style or nature, sublime; of high intellectual or moral value.
(of a gas etc.) Less dense than usual; thin.
examples: The air at high altitudes at the top of mountains is rarefied.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of rarefy
